Q4)Integrating Webhooks for CI/CD Automation------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Task-----
Expected Output:
Jenkins Pipeline triggered automatically via GitHub Webhook without manual or SCM polling


Create Jenkinsfile in GitHub repo/
node {
    properties([
        pipelineTriggers([
            [$class: 'GitHubPushTrigger']
        ])
    ])

    stage('Build') {
        bat 'mvn clean install'
    }

    stage('Test') {
        bat 'mvn test'
    }

    stage('Deploy') {
        bat 'echo Deployment Completed'
    }
}
Commit & Push to GitHub.
Create a new Pipeline Job in Jenkins

STEP 3: Configure Jenkins to use your Jenkinsfile (from GitHub)

Inside the job:

Scroll to Pipeline section:

Definition: Pipeline script from SCM

SCM: Git

Repository URL: your GitHub repo URL

STEP 4: Enable the webhook trigger

Scroll up to Build Triggers:

✔ Check → GitHub hook trigger for GITScm polling

This is important!

ngrok http 8080
https://abcd1234.ngrok-free.app/github-webhook/
Go to GitHub:

Your Repo → Settings → Webhooks → Add Webhook

Fill:

Field	Value
Payload URL	http://<jenkins-url>/github-webhook/
Content Type	application/json
Event	Just the push event
Secret	leave empty

Now go to your repo → make a small change → push.

Example:

git commit -m "webhook test"
git push


email configuration:------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Manage Jenkins → Configure System
Scroll to Email Notification

SMTP Server:smtp.gmail.com
✔ Use SMTP Authentication:

Check ✔

✔ Username:

Your Gmail

yourname@gmail.com
✔ Password:

⚠ IMPORTANT: Gmail requires an App Password, NOT your normal password.

If you are using a temporary Gmail for exam:

Go to Google Account

Security

Enable 2-Step Verification

Go to App Passwords

Choose "Mail" + "Windows Computer"

Copy the generated 16-digit password

Paste that in Jenkins.
Advanced Settings (Required for Gmail)

Click Advanced

Set:

Field	Value
SMTP Port	587
Use TLS	✔ Enabled
Use SSL	❌ Not needed

Save the configuration.

STEP 3: Test the email

Scroll to:

"Send Test Email"

Enter your Gmail:

yourname@gmail.com


Click Test.

If everything is correct, you will receive a test email.------------------------------
Q4)Jenkins Email Notification Configuration
Task-----
Expected Output:Jenkins sends an email notification on build failure to the configured recipient list

1️⃣ Configure Email in Jenkins (SMTP Settings)
In Jenkins:
Manage Jenkins → Configure System → Email Notification
Fill:
SMTP Server: smtp.gmail.com
Use SMTP Authentication: ✔
Username: your Gmail ID
Password: Gmail App Password
SMTP Port: 587
Use TLS: ✔
Save.
jenkinsfile for Email on FAILURE Only
node {
    stage('Build') {
        bat 'mvn clean install'
    }

    stage('Test') {
        // forcing failure for testing
        bat 'exit 1'
    }
}

post {
    failure {
        mail to: 'recipient@gmail.com',
             subject: 'Jenkins Build Failed',
             body: 'The Jenkins build has failed. Please check console logs.'
    }
}
